		<td><b>Original Apple II Prince of Persia's source code released</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />For all of you ASM coder out there, you might be happy to hear the the original Apple II source code for Prince of Persia was released a few days ago. The author believed the source to be lost for decades before catching a lucky break and finding some 3.5'' floppy in an old box. You can read about this interesting story at <a href="http://jordanmechner.com/blog/2012/04/source/" class="postlink">http://jordanmechner.com/blog/2012/04/source/</a> and download the source from github. There's also documentation available explaining some part of it. I am no programmer but I am sure this would be something fun to check out if I knew any ASM. Now I'm hoping someone will get cracking on a Vectrex port <img src="./images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


