	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Re: fluidity of motion in original PoP: I forget where I read this (probably an Apple II magazine like BYTE or similar), but I believe the fluidity stems from Jordan Mechner's desire to provide very smooth animations for his bitmaps (e.g. single-pixel changes, thus lots of frames).
<br />
<br />This stems from an earlier game Justin worked on/wrote, called Karateka, where to get the animations looking accurate and smooth -- and this is what I remember reading specifically -- he travelled and actually watched martial artists practise/spar.  I'm certain he took that same knowledge and applied it to PoP.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


